All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Employee
The Employee class serves as an abstract base class for different types of employees.
EmployeeBuilder
The EmployeeBuilder interface defines a builder pattern for creating Employee objects.
EmployeeDirector
The EmployeeDirector class is responsible for directing the construction of Employee objects using the EmployeeBuilder interface.
EmployeeFactory
The EmployeeFactory class provides a factory method for creating different types of Employee objects based on the provided type.
EmployeeManager
The EmployeeManager class is a singleton that manages a collection of Employee objects.
EMS
The EMS class serves as the entry point for the Employee Management System.
FullTimeEmployee
The FullTimeEmployee class represents a full-time employee and extends the abstract Employee class.
FullTimeEmployeeBuilder
The FullTimeEmployeeBuilder class implements the EmployeeBuilder interface to provide a concrete builder for creating FullTimeEmployee objects.
PartTimeEmployee
The PartTimeEmployee class represents a part-time employee and extends the abstract Employee class.
PartTimeEmployeeBuilder
The PartTimeEmployeeBuilder class implements the EmployeeBuilder interface to provide a concrete builder for creating PartTimeEmployee objects.
